object.doc: Represents a document which places an order with a deliverer of services.
Remember to define ToCurr derived association in the derived classes, either as a derived expression or in the code.

Abstract class representing an order from a customer.
Class representing a calculated expected cost of an executed item.
Class representing a calculated price of an executed item.
Class representing a service from an customer's order.
Class representing a difference between real cost and expected cost while connecting costs in controlling.
Represents invoiced service. For InInvoices this should provide all kinds of single ExecutedItem details. For OutInvoice this should be linked with single ExecutedService.

Class representing an object which is created when an object of InInvoiceAmount class is connected to an object of ExecutedItemCost class. It happens when a real cost from incoming invoice is connected to an expected cost from a customer's order.
Represents a cost or price of invoiced service.
Abstract class representing an executed item which corresponds to services accomplished by deliverers for our customers. It can be registered in a customer order.

Represents a contractor which is a Deliverer.
Note: Deliverer should have all deliverer related properties (Ubezpieczenia, konta bankowe, ...). These properties are now improperly located in Company.
